Heat the oil in a large saucepan over a medium heat. Add the cumin, black mustard seeds, garlic, ginger, onions, turmeric and chillies and fry for 1–2 minutes. Add the tomatoes and cook for 10–12 minutes.Remove any skin from the chicken and add the thighs to the pan. Cook for 20–30 minutes, or until cooked through. Stir in the garam masala and season with salt. Garnish with coriander and serve.